{
  "text": "Most of these effects are likely to emanate from circulating catecholamines, since denervation does not affect hypothermia-induced decrease in renal blood flow [CITATION_1] . Indeed, previous studies in human kidneys have shown that intra-renaladrenoceptors mediate a tonic renal vasoconstriction (1, 15, 35 ).",
